# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.example` and configure your values:

```bash
# Required Configuration
SMTP2GO_API_KEY=your-smtp2go-api-key-here
TO_EMAIL=contact@yourdomain.com

# Optional Configuration  
FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
FROM_NAME=Contact Form
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://yourdomain.com,https://www.yourdomain.com
SUBJECT_PREFIX=[Contact Form]

# Validation Settings
REQUIRED_FIELDS=name,email,message
MAX_MESSAGE_LENGTH=5000

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=10
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=300

# Custom Messages
SUCCESS_MESSAGE=Thank you for your message. We will get back to you soon!
ERROR_MESSAGE=Sorry, there was an error sending your message. Please try again.
```

## Setting Secrets in Cloudflare

Use wrangler to set sensitive values:

```bash
wrangler secret put SMTP2GO_API_KEY
wrangler secret put TO_EMAIL
wrangler secret put FROM_EMAIL
wrangler secret put ALLOWED_ORIGINS
```

## Development vs Production

For local development, you can use a `.env` file (not recommended for production):

```bash
# .env (local development only)
SMTP2GO_API_KEY=your-dev-api-key
TO_EMAIL=dev@yourdomain.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
```

For production, always use Cloudflare secrets or environment variables in the dashboard.